        "created_at": "2021-09-09T21:57:04.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=3033193\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2017 Domaine Bernard Moreau et Fils Chassagne-Montrachet 1er Cru Morgeot La Cardeuse Rouge</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Chassagne-Montrachet 1er Cru (9/9/2021)</em><br>\nVibrant red fruit. Like a wonderful old Burgundy in many ways. Especially the purity of fruit.   Still some structure to resolve in the mid palate but the core of fruit on the finish is bright red and intense. Very long and refreshing.   I can only imagine what another 5 years of bottle age will do here. Fantastic!</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em>  Folks.  This is a great wine!</p>",
